						<summary>

						<p>Slab at the entrance (inside) into the Narasiṁhasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1784, Durmati, Phālguṇa śu. 12,</hi> corresponding to 1862 A.D., March 13, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a <hi rend="italic">kalyāṇa-maṇḍapa</hi> to the god Lakshmi Narasimhasvāmi by Kṛishnṇamaśeṭṭi, son of Subbiseṭṭi and grandson of Kaṁdula Guruvappa of Yeliseṭṭi <hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> of the Vaiśyas.</p>						

						</summary>
